> Parmigiana is an Italian dish made with roasted or fried aubergine layered with
> tomato sauce and cheese before being baked. Our Aubergine Parmigiana Style
> Traybake is a simpler version, but still full of flavour.

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @aubergine{2}, then slice into rounds approximately 1cm thick.

Pop the aubergine onto a medium baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over
the @mixed herbs{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

In a small #bowl{}, mix together the @marinara sauce{120%grams} and @honey{1%tbsp}.

When the aubergine has 5 mins remaining, remove the tray from the oven. Pour over
the marinara sauce and sprinkle evenly with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{60%grams}.

Return to the oven until the sauce is piping hot and the cheese has melted,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Share the aubergine parmigiana between your plates. Spoon over any remaining
sauce and cheese from the tray.

Serve the roasted potatoes and @baby leaf mix{50%grams} alongside. Drizzle some
@oil{} and the @balsamic glaze{12%milliliters} over the leaves.

Serve with @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} for dipping.

Enjoy!